HEADWORD: Owler
<hw>Owl"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Owl</er>,
<pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <def>One who owls; esp., one who conveys
contraband goods. See <er>Owling</er>, <pos>n.</pos></def> <mark>[Obs.
or Prov. Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>T. Brown.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
